Adult sexually explicit comic. It's unclear exactly when the comic was first released but it's widely assumed to be the early 70's.

In true style with the notorious Tijuana Bible this comic lives up to it's name and has some pun-filled porn with some chaste sexless family favorites that could never get away with having sex in their own comics. There's a whole line of character names that are meant to emulate their sexless counterparts.

Brenda Starr becomes Brenda Stack, Archy becomes Starchie, Snuffy Smith becomes Sniffy Muff and there are more to find.

It's a cheerful comic and more true to the standards of the earlier pornographic comics as noted by the fact that they even censored the name of the comic.

The comic holds 68 pages and stories are completely black and white. Artist and writer are uncredited and the publisher is also unknown. It was released in the United States and only ran one issue.

Dilton in "Drop-Out!" Part 4. Dilton's amazing computer chip design has been ripped off by Snarley Tech! What's a boy genius to do? Dilton's brush with adulthood wraps up with a twist you won't believe!
name: Drop Out! Conclusion

description: The Scribblenauts gang travels to Metropolis where they find a mob of anti-Superman protesters led by--Lois Lane and Jimmy Olsen?! The Man of Steel himself has no idea why his best pals have turned against him...so it's up to Maxwell and Lily to solve this puzzle!
name: The City That Hated Superman

volume.name: Scribblenauts Unmasked: A Crisis of Imagination

description: Before she was a part of Josie & the Pussycats, she was just Josie! See how this world-famous rock star started out -- as an average high school teen! With her BFFs, the ditzy Melody and the quick and witty Pepper, Josie gets caught up in all sorts of misadventures. Check out this 100-page Digital Exclusive and meet her boyfriend Albert, the rotten Cabot twins Alex and Alexandra, and many more!

Three soldiers, one French, one Belgian and one British, meet in the trenches of WWI. They've just countered the first attacks of the Germans at the Yzer front. They spend the day together on November 1, 1914 and agree to see each other again at the same spot in exactly 10 years. If they survive the war, that is. This is the story of three men, three soldiers with their own history and the three lives they have led: before, during and after the Great War. A dramatic story, enforced by the beautiful drawings of Ivan Petrus.

All of the costumes and details illustrated in this graphic novel are historically correct.

Hardcover, 128 pages, 22x27cm.

person_credits.name: Kim Deitch
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description:
This is a true story, brought back to life by the author and artist Ivan Petrus Adrianssen.

Elsie Knocker and Mairi Chisholm are two British women. They volunteer for the wounded soldiers ambulance corps during WWI. They work together closely and share everything. To help the wounded soldiers even faster they start their own bandage post at the front-line at Pervijze. Their 'Celler House' becomes very well known by the soldiers fighting the war and they are refereed to as 'The Angels of Pervijze'.

The war takes it's toll on the two women. Will their friendship survive the war?

Bound edition, 22x27cm, 130 pages.
name: Engelen van Flanders Fields

volume.name: Shades of Gray Comics and Stories

description:
In the last remaining Victorian house of what was once the most beautiful district of the city lives Alice. The house is an orphanage, where she brings up Vic, Trish, Jay-jay, Gri-Gri and Sharp.

Alice and her orphans are surrounded by faceless skyscrapers, built by multi-billionaire Hari Vallalkozo. He has bought every remaining house, only Alice refuses every bid. This way he cannot start building his magnum opus : the V-building, the largest skyscraper in the world.

Alice and her orphans must fight the dominance of the vertical concrete...

English title: Get out of Town!
name: Inpakken en Wegwezen!

description:
Hari Vallalkozo’s men have dug a giant pit around Alice’s ground, leaving the pat of soil hanging above a giant pit. It is suspended only by water and sewage drains. Alice and the orphans will have to adapt to these circumstances. They go and see the mayor, but he turns out to have been bribed by Vallalkozo. When they go to confront the billionaire face to face, a Vallalkozo demolition man is already at work near their house. Bruno the dog and Minky the ermine are forced to defend the orphanage with everything that resembles a weapon…

English title: Pat Sweet Pat
name: Oost West, Kluit Best!

description:
The children fear a new Vallalkozo-attack, and decide to take turns at night-guarding the house from the treehouse. Meanwhile, Alice has lost her Beatles ‘White Album’.

Hari hires a new assistant, who advises him to contact Alice in order to charm her into a sale of her house. Hari likes the sound of this, because he has fallen head over heels in love with his nemesis…

English title: The White Album.
name: Het Witte Album

description:
A TV special was shot near the pat, but the house was never filmed. Instead, Hari Vallalkozo was allowed to show his building plans to the public. He offers Alice pots of cash for the house, but she keeps refusing the sale. Meanwhile, she gets invited for a remembrance service at sea for Jim-Jim. The orphans are left all alone for an exciting Halloween night...

English title: Soil, Sea and Sky.
name: Te Land, ter Zee en in de Vlucht!

description:
Nothing's working out for Hari Vallalkozo. Alice refuses to sell her house, she refuses his proposal of marriage, his investors are lketting him down and - worst of all - his ex-wife appears without warning.

Suddenly a piece of the pad, on which the house is standing, breakes off. Alice is panicking and decides to sell the house.


English title: Bric on Bric, Plank on Plank.
name: Steen op Steen, Plank op Plank

description:
Alice appears to have lost her house for ever. In an attempt to gain it back the children get scattered. All of them have an idea on how to play a dirty trick on Vallalkozo who has a new demolisher on the job. This one is absolutely keen on putting his claws into Alices house. New bosses Hanz and Ursula are the spectators in a conflict that reaches a climax...

English title: Bye, Bye Pat
name: Bye Bye, Kluit

description:
Alice and the orphans are free like a bird. They escaped the skyscraper city of Hari Vallalkozo on board of a giant hot air balloon. They didn't left the house behind, it's also attached to the balloon.

They are heading to a Caribbean island Alice received as a gift from Hari. He wanted to trade the house for it and, at the same time, conquer her heart.

But Hari sets off in pursuit of her, and he has more than one reason to do so...

English title: Orphans from the Wind
name: De Wezen van de Wind

description:
The hot air balloon from Alice and the orphans is catched by a havy storm. Lightning strucks the engines, it's all hens on deck to save the house and themselves from falling down in the ocean!

Hari Vallalkozo has all the difficulties of the world to follow them. All hope is gone to catch up with Alice, until he receives the visit of an unannounced guest...

Englis title: The Son of Vallalkozo.
name: De Zoon van Vallalkozo

description:
The Orphans are on their way to the island given by Vallalkozo to Alice. While in pursuit of his beloved, Vallalkozo and his comrades crash on a WW2 run ashore aircraft carrier. They are welcomed by a Japanese kamikaze pilot who survived for 60 years on the rusted vessel. He thinks help finally arrived!

While the Blériot brothers try to fix one of the remaining airplanes aboard the carrier, the orphans battle with a whaler in order to save the whales from being slaughtered. Meanwhile, on the home front, Ursula is taking control over Vallalkozo's concrete empire...

English title: Banzaï Whales!
name: Banzaï Potvis!

description:
An unexpected nightly breeze blows the orphans' balloon to the north instead of the south, to the shores of Greenland, not far from the last location mentioned in the second diary of uncle Archibald, the explorer.

There, a big surprise awaits them...

Meanwhile Vallalkozo has decided to join Alice on the island, and leaves his entire business in the hands of his assistant Hanz.

Not his smartest move...

English title: Can't get any Whiter!
name: Nu nog Witter!

description:
Alice and the orphans hear that Zemeckis, big boss of Z-oil, is on his Zupa Oil Rig which is located not far from Alices island.

She decides to go there and ask him in person about the disappearence of her beloved Jimjim, now 30 years ago.

But she is not the only one to arrive on the oil rig. Vallalkozo joins the party and so does Hanz. The great clash of the titans can begin.

Will the kids be able to help their adoptive mother and find the truth about Jimjim?

English title: The Black Album.
name: Het Zwarte Album

description:
It seems like time stood still.

Alice is back together with her loved one, Jimjim!

They are once again ready to confront the super-polluter Douglas Zemeckis and his company Z-Oil and shut it down once and for all.

But during the past 30 years Z-Oil has grown into a giant and corrupt industry that intends to make money by sending tons of waste to the planet Mars.

In order to defeat Z-Oil, Alice and Jimjim need the orphans, but where on the oil platform does Zemeckis keep them imprisoned?

English title: Be Mine!
name: Wees de Mijne!

volume.name: The Legends of NASCAR Christmas Special

description:
In December 1941, the same month of the infamous Pearl Harbor attack in real history, the biggest and the most powerful battleship in the world, the IMS Yamato, was secretly commissioned. So secretly, in fact, that most of the people in Japan didn't even know of its existence until after World War II, when it no longer existed!

The Yamato was designated as "Special Battleship Number 1" for most of those who actually got to see it during wartime. Only the crew and other special people knew its real name, taken from the old name for Japan and its people in the current province.

The "Yamato-Damashii," or Yamato Spirit, is the cause the Japanese used to fight a desperate war, a war that they feared might end the Japanese as a race. With this conviction, the Kamikaze forces threw everything they had against the invading military, including the battleship itself. But in this altered war, the Yamato and her sister ships will fight an even more deadly game, because the United States were unable to prepare their atomic bombs against Hiroshima and Nagasaki.

description: A sweeping visual tale of Gotham City’s forgotten citizens: the abused and the voiceless. Will these desperate souls find their angel in The Dark Knight? Find out in this special mostly silent issue.
name: Voiceless, Part One of Two

description: Kate Kane's life has always been one of intrigue and adventure, but since she took on the mantle of Batwoman, things have been in overdrive with no sign of slowing down! Join us as Batwoman starts her next chapter and faces a threat that might just have her rethinking her career as a hero!
name: Webs, Part One: Strands

description: Damian Wayne has been bruised and beaten to a pulp…but nothing before will compare to his latest confrontation with the horde of villains in this issue. When pitted against Professor Pyg, DC villain’s month darling Jakanapes and other baddies, how will Damian survive—especially when he finds a certain clown waiting for him at the finish line?
name: Book Three: If Animals Could Talk

description: The Court of Owls’ machinations threaten to tear Gotham City apart, and no one but Calvin Rose can take them down once and for all!
name: End of the Run

description: “Sea of Storms” begins with the debut of new AQUAMAN writer Jeff Parker! The Earth’s crust is grinding to life, releasing deadly volcanoes and bizarre creatures…so humanity’s first instinct is to blame Atlantis! And as the plates pull apart, the pressures of ruling a kingdom under siege are weighing on Aquaman and Mera as well!
name: Pressure

description: A FOREVER EVIL tie-in! The Crime Syndicate’s Sea King, last seen at the end of “Trinity War,” has cheated death and plagues the JL Dark team!
name: Forever Evil: Blight - The Haunted Sea

description: A RED WILL BE DEAD! It’s Guy Gardner and five Red Lanterns on their first mission in Sector 2814—a planetary army a billion strong, led by the evil fascist dictator Field Marshal Gensui. How can they all possibly survive? In fact, not all of them do!
name: Red. Dead.
